{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"This is one of the most amazing animals\non the face of the Earth."},{"time":6840,"text":"This is a tapir."},{"time":8960,"text":"Now this, this is a baby tapir,"},{"time":12640,"text":"the cutest animal offspring\nin the animal kingdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"By far."},{"time":19600,"text":"There is no competition here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23520,"text":"I have dedicated\nthe past 20 years of my life"},{"time":26240,"text":"to the research and conservation\nof tapirs in Brazil,"},{"time":29440,"text":"and it has been absolutely amazing."},{"time":33160,"text":"But at the moment,\nI've been thinking really, really hard"},{"time":36680,"text":"about the impact of my work."},{"time":39120,"text":"I've been questioning myself\nabout the real contributions I have made"},{"time":43240,"text":"for the conservation\nof these animals I love so much."},{"time":46800,"text":"Am I being effective"},{"time":48680,"text":"in safeguarding their survival?"},{"time":51680,"text":"Am I doing enough?"},{"time":54040,"text":"I guess the big question here is,"},{"time":56360,"text":"am I studying tapirs\nand contributing to their conservation,"},{"time":61760,"text":"or am I just documenting their extinction?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65760,"text":"The world is facing\nso many different conservation crises."},{"time":69720,"text":"We all know that.\nIt's all over the news every day."},{"time":73080,"text":"Tropical forests and other ecosystems\nare being destroyed,"},{"time":77400,"text":"climate change, so many species\non the brink of extinction:"},{"time":81680,"text":"tigers, lions, elephants, rhinos, tapirs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88240,"text":"This is the lowland tapir,\nthe tapir species I work with,"},{"time":91960,"text":"the largest terrestrial mammal\nof South America."},{"time":95120,"text":"They're massive. They're powerful."},{"time":97680,"text":"Adults can weigh up to 300 kilos."},{"time":100240,"text":"That's half the size of a horse."},{"time":102360,"text":"They're gorgeous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104200,"text":"Tapirs are mostly found\nin tropical forests such as the Amazon,"},{"time":109120,"text":"and they absolutely need\nlarge patches of habitat"},{"time":113600,"text":"in order to find all the resources\nthey need to reproduce and survive."},{"time":119160,"text":"But their habitat is being destroyed,"},{"time":122120,"text":"and they have been hunted out of several\nparts of their geographic distribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127640,"text":"And you see, this is\nvery, very unfortunate"},{"time":131400,"text":"because tapirs are extremely important\nfor the habitats where they are found."},{"time":135800,"text":"They're herbivores."},{"time":137200,"text":"Fifty percent of their diet\nconsists of fruit,"},{"time":140560,"text":"and when they eat the fruit,\nthey swallow the seeds,"},{"time":143480,"text":"which they disperse throughout\nthe habitat through their feces."},{"time":147120,"text":"They play this major role\nin shaping and maintaining"},{"time":151680,"text":"the structure and diversity of the forest,"},{"time":155160,"text":"and for that reason, tapirs are known\nas gardeners of the forest."},{"time":161320,"text":"Isn't that amazing?"},{"time":163080,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":164920,"text":"the extinction of tapirs\nwould seriously affect"},{"time":168000,"text":"biodiversity as a whole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170920,"text":"I started my tapir work in 1996,\nstill very young, fresh out of college,"},{"time":176840,"text":"and it was a pioneer research\nand conservation program."},{"time":180200,"text":"At that point, we had nearly\nzero information about tapirs,"},{"time":183560,"text":"mostly because they're\nso difficult to study."},{"time":186880,"text":"They're nocturnal, solitary,\nvery elusive animals,"},{"time":191440,"text":"and we got started getting\nvery basic data about these animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196640,"text":"But what is it\nthat a conservationist does?"},{"time":200520,"text":"Well, first, we need data."},{"time":202800,"text":"We need field research."},{"time":204400,"text":"We need those long-term datasets\nto support conservation action,"},{"time":209040,"text":"and I told you tapirs\nare very hard to study,"},{"time":212080,"text":"so we have to rely\non indirect methods to study them."},{"time":216040,"text":"We have to capture and anesthetize them"},{"time":218760,"text":"so that we can install GPS collars\naround their necks"},{"time":222240,"text":"and follow their movements,"},{"time":223920,"text":"which is a technique used by many\nother conservationists around the world."},{"time":228360,"text":"And then we can gather information\nabout how they use space,"},{"time":232320,"text":"how they move through the landscape,"},{"time":234400,"text":"what are their priority habitats,"},{"time":236400,"text":"and so much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238480,"text":"Next, we must disseminate what we learn."},{"time":242440,"text":"We have to educate people about tapirs"},{"time":245160,"text":"and how important these animals are."},{"time":247800,"text":"And it's amazing\nhow many people around the world"},{"time":251440,"text":"do not know what a tapir is."},{"time":254280,"text":"In fact, many people think\nthis is a tapir."},{"time":258920,"text":"Let me tell you, this is not a tapir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262880,"text":"This is a giant anteater."},{"time":264840,"text":"Tapirs do not eat ants. Never. Ever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270440,"text":"And then next we have to provide\ntraining, capacity building."},{"time":275200,"text":"It is our responsibility to prepare\nthe conservationists of the future."},{"time":279680,"text":"We are losing several\nconservation battles,"},{"time":282760,"text":"and we need more people doing what we do,"},{"time":285240,"text":"and they need the skills,\nand they need the passion to do that."},{"time":289640,"text":"Ultimately, we conservationists,"},{"time":292200,"text":"we must be able to apply our data,"},{"time":294840,"text":"to apply our accumulated knowledge"},{"time":297080,"text":"to support actual conservation action."},{"time":301040,"text":"Our first tapir program"},{"time":303040,"text":"took place in the Atlantic Forest"},{"time":305320,"text":"in the eastern part of Brazil,"},{"time":307480,"text":"one of the most threatened\nbiomes in the world."},{"time":310880,"text":"The destruction of the Atlantic Forest"},{"time":313080,"text":"began in the early 1500s,"},{"time":315320,"text":"when the Portuguese\nfirst arrived in Brazil,"},{"time":318120,"text":"beginning European colonization\nin the eastern part of South America."},{"time":322560,"text":"This forest was almost completely cleared"},{"time":325880,"text":"for timber, agriculture, cattle ranching\nand the construction of cities,"},{"time":331120,"text":"and today only seven percent\nof the Atlantic forest"},{"time":334600,"text":"is still left standing."},{"time":336800,"text":"And tapirs are found in very, very small,\nisolated, disconnected populations."},{"time":343200,"text":"In the Atlantic Forest, we found out\nthat tapirs move through open areas"},{"time":347880,"text":"of pastureland and agriculture"},{"time":350240,"text":"going from one patch of forest\nto patch of forest."},{"time":354480,"text":"So our main approach in this region"},{"time":357040,"text":"was to use our tapir data\nto identify the potential places"},{"time":361440,"text":"for the establishment\nof wildlife corridors"},{"time":364440,"text":"in between those patches of forest,"},{"time":367120,"text":"reconnecting the habitat"},{"time":369200,"text":"so that tapirs and many other animals\ncould cross the landscape safely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373960,"text":"After 12 years in the Atlantic Forest,"},{"time":376720,"text":"in 2008, we expanded our tapir\nconservation efforts to the Pantanal"},{"time":381760,"text":"in the western part of Brazil"},{"time":383760,"text":"near the border with Bolivia and Paraguay."},{"time":387160,"text":"This is the largest continuous\nfreshwater floodplain in the world,"},{"time":392600,"text":"an incredible place"},{"time":394080,"text":"and one of the most important strongholds\nfor lowland tapirs in South America."},{"time":398760,"text":"And working in the Pantanal\nhas been extremely refreshing"},{"time":403280,"text":"because we found large,\nhealthy tapir populations in the area,"},{"time":407280,"text":"and we have been able to study tapirs"},{"time":409240,"text":"in the most natural conditions\nwe'll ever find,"},{"time":413000,"text":"very much free of threats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416280,"text":"In the Pantanal, besides the GPS collars,\nwe are using another technique:"},{"time":421000,"text":"camera traps."},{"time":422240,"text":"This camera is equipped\nwith a movement sensor"},{"time":425160,"text":"and it photographs animals\nwhen they walk in front of it."},{"time":428200,"text":"So thanks to these amazing devices,"},{"time":430680,"text":"we have been able\nto gather precious information"},{"time":433920,"text":"about tapir reproduction\nand social organization"},{"time":436880,"text":"which are very important\npieces of the puzzle"},{"time":439440,"text":"when you're trying to develop\nthose conservation strategies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443560,"text":"And right now, 2015,\nwe are expanding our work once again"},{"time":448280,"text":"to the Brazilian Cerrado,"},{"time":450160,"text":"the open grasslands and shrub forests\nin the central part of Brazil."},{"time":454360,"text":"Today this region is the very epicenter\nof economic development in my country,"},{"time":461280,"text":"where natural habitat\nand wildlife populations"},{"time":464000,"text":"are rapidly being eradicated\nby several different threats,"},{"time":468120,"text":"including once again cattle ranching,"},{"time":470720,"text":"large sugarcane and soybean plantations,"},{"time":473480,"text":"poaching, roadkill, just to name a few."},{"time":477000,"text":"And somehow, tapirs are still there,"},{"time":480640,"text":"which gives me a lot of hope."},{"time":483080,"text":"But I have to say that starting\nthis new program in the Cerrado"},{"time":487600,"text":"was a bit of a slap in the face."},{"time":490480,"text":"When you drive around"},{"time":491960,"text":"and you find dead tapirs\nalong the highways"},{"time":495800,"text":"and signs of tapirs wandering around\nin the middle of sugarcane plantations"},{"time":500840,"text":"where they shouldn't be,"},{"time":502880,"text":"and you talk to kids and they tell you\nthat they know how tapir meat tastes"},{"time":507120,"text":"because their families poach and eat them,"},{"time":510520,"text":"it really breaks your heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514039,"text":"The situation in the Cerrado\nmade me realize --"},{"time":517280,"text":"it gave me the sense of urgency."},{"time":520240,"text":"I am swimming against the tide."},{"time":522559,"text":"It made me realize that despite\ntwo decades of hard work"},{"time":526240,"text":"trying to save these animals,\nwe still have so much work to do"},{"time":529800,"text":"if we are to prevent them\nfrom disappearing."},{"time":532880,"text":"We have to find ways\nto solve all these problems."},{"time":536840,"text":"We really do, and you know what?"},{"time":538720,"text":"We really came to a point\nin the conservation world"},{"time":542160,"text":"where we have to think out of the box."},{"time":544920,"text":"We'll have to be a lot more creative\nthan we are right now."},{"time":548680,"text":"And I told you, roadkill is a big problem\nfor tapirs in the Cerrado,"},{"time":552600,"text":"so we just came up with the idea\nof putting reflective stickers"},{"time":556040,"text":"on the GPS collars we put on the tapirs."},{"time":558880,"text":"These are the same stickers\nused on big trucks"},{"time":561240,"text":"to avoid collision."},{"time":562880,"text":"Tapirs cross the highways after dark,"},{"time":566120,"text":"so the stickers will hopefully\nhelp drivers see this shining thing"},{"time":571320,"text":"crossing the highway,"},{"time":572760,"text":"and maybe they will\nslow down a little bit."},{"time":576320,"text":"For now, this is just a crazy idea."},{"time":578920,"text":"We don't know. We'll see if it will\nreduce the amount of tapir roadkill."},{"time":583600,"text":"But the point is, maybe this is\nthe kind of stuff that needs to be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588920,"text":"And although I'm struggling\nwith all these questions"},{"time":592680,"text":"in my mind right now,"},{"time":595480,"text":"I have a pact with tapirs."},{"time":598400,"text":"I know in my heart"},{"time":600160,"text":"that tapir conservation is my cause."},{"time":603120,"text":"This is my passion."},{"time":604840,"text":"I am not alone."},{"time":606400,"text":"I have this huge network\nof supporters behind me,"},{"time":610160,"text":"and there is no way\nI'm ever going to stop."},{"time":613200,"text":"I will continue doing this,\nmost probably for the rest of my life."},{"time":617600,"text":"And I'll keep doing this\nfor Patrícia, my namesake,"},{"time":621920,"text":"one of the first tapirs we captured\nand monitored in the Atlantic Forest"},{"time":625720,"text":"many, many years ago;"},{"time":627840,"text":"for Rita and her baby Vincent\nin the Pantanal."},{"time":632400,"text":"And I'll keep doing this for Ted,\na baby tapir we captured"},{"time":636520,"text":"in December last year\nalso in the Pantanal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639960,"text":"And I will keep doing this"},{"time":642080,"text":"for the hundreds of tapirs\nthat I've had the pleasure to meet"},{"time":645760,"text":"over the years"},{"time":647000,"text":"and the many others I know\nI will encounter in the future."},{"time":650560,"text":"These animals deserve to be cared for."},{"time":653920,"text":"They need me. They need us."},{"time":656920,"text":"And you know? We human beings\ndeserve to live in a world"},{"time":661920,"text":"where we can get out there\nand see and benefit from"},{"time":665840,"text":"not only tapirs"},{"time":667520,"text":"but all the other beautiful species,"},{"time":670360,"text":"now and in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673200,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675320,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}